Set module¶

This Python script implements a set using hashes.

It does it’s best for the average time complexity to be O(1) to O(n) for most of the operations

For the worst case scenarios (where there are hash collisions), the time complexity for those operations increases to O(n) to O(n²)

class Set.Set(param=None)¶

Bases: object

__hash__() → int¶

Generate a hash of this Set using FNV1A hash

Makes a copy of this Set and uses FNV1A hash with a little tweak (I use modulo 1E19 just so numbers don’t get TOO big)

Returns

This Set’s hash code

Return type

int

Hint

Time complexity: O(n)
